   <text type="letter">
      <body>
         
            <opener>
               <dateline rend="right">
                  <name type="place">Washington</name>
                  <date when="1865-06-09">June 9, 1865.<ptr target="med.00312_n100"/>
               </date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>My dear friend,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>The <hi rend="italic">Homer</hi>
               <ptr target="med.00312_n2"/> has come &amp; is now lying before me. I thank you deeply. I am very well, this summer, &amp; go to the Hospitals daily &amp; nightly&#8212;as I find a greater proportion of sad cases than ever&#8212;&amp; for some reason or other there are few or no visitors. I enjoy my visits with a sad but profound joy &amp; satisfaction&#8212;especially at night, when the light is nearly turned off, &amp; I am soothing some suffering one.</p>
            <p>I send you, same mail with this, two copies of the little book Drum-Taps. Farewell.</p>
            <closer rend="right">
               <signed>Walt Whitman<ptr target="med.00312_n3"/>
               </signed>
            </closer> 
         
      </body>
